My comment on Twitter was made after the stark revelation of the bomb mailings to Obama, Clinton. It remains my view that @realdonaldtrump may have stoked this by labeling his opponents and the media as "enemies of the people." "Lock them up" became a recurring theme.

"Knock the crap out of them... I would like to punch them in their face" was a familiar refrain at his rallies. As Republican strategist Schmidt said last night: "His rallies brim with menace... That someone would seek to kill their political enemies is not aberrational
but rather the inevitable consequence of Trump's incitement." When pro Trumpers defended the President, they responded that Eric Holder said this in October: “When they go low, we kick them.”

But this is negative data mining, incomplete and failed to write that Holder quickly added in the same speech: "When I say we kick them, I don’t mean we do anything inappropriate, we don’t do anything illegal, but we have to be tough and we have to fight."
This is the end of my conversation/thread on this subject.
